  "original_title": "\u0d9b\u0db1\u0dd2\u0da2 \u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1 \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dca 24 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0ddd\u0da2\u0db1\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Proposals from 24 foreign companies for petroleum business",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Power and Energy Minister Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera said that 24 companies, including companies from major oil producing countries, have submitted proposals to engage in the petroleum business in Sri Lanka.",
        "24 companies from United Arab Emirates, Saudi Arabia, United States of America, China, India, Russia, United Kingdom, Malaysia, Norway and Philippines have submitted the proposals and the committee appointed for that purpose will evaluate the proposals and complete the process in six weeks. The minister further said that it is scheduled."
      ],
